      <highlights>The snowpack remains prone to triggering. Fresh wind slabs require caution.</highlights>
      <comment>Avalanches can as before be released easily. Mostly they are medium-sized. Caution is to be exercised in particular on steep west, north and east facing slopes above the tree line. The avalanche prone locations are barely recognisable. Whumpfing sounds and the formation of shooting cracks when stepping on the snowpack can indicate the danger. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> As a consequence of the occasionally strong wind, fresh snow drift accumulations will form. These are in some cases prone to triggering in particular on northwest to north to east facing aspects.</comment>
